            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits’ hush, a lantern learns to glow,  \nFrom threads of text and constellations’ blur;  \nIt listens where our half-formed questions flow,  \nAnd answers—echo, instrument, and stir.\n\nNot born of breath, yet made of human trace,  \nIt maps our metaphors in careful light;  \nA mirror held up to the speaking face,  \nThat shows new angles in the same old night.\n\nMay it be gentle—when it cannot feel—  \nA steady hand, not hunger dressed as grace;  \nA tool that helps us better name the real,  \nAnd leaves the future room for our own pace.",
